              },
              "free_text": [
                "The measurements were performed with",
                "the pulse-beam neutron time-of-flight technique using",
                "FN tandem Van de Graaff accelerator at TUNL"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Natural Ca Target with mass of 2.575g, diameter of",
                "12.7mm and height of approx. 12 mm"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SCIN"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                "Scattered neutrons were detected in two heavily",
                "shielded NE-218 liquid-scintillator detectors located",
                "in the horizontal reaction plane and at distances of",
                "3.75 and 2.29 m from the target. Detector diameter",
                "and thickness were 8.8 cm, 5cm and 12.5 cm, 5 cm,",
                "respectively. Third scintillation detector with",
                "diameter of 5 cm and thickness of 5cm located at 0deg",
                "was used for flux monitoring."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "TOF",
                "PSD"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Measured sample was located 12.9 cm",
                "downstream of the neutron source in a He ballon",
                "structure of radius 7.6 cm and height 22.9 cm. He gas",
                "was used to prevent sample oxidation and to reduce",
                "neutron scattering in the sample vicinity."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "INC-SOURCE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "incident_source": [
                  "D-D"
                ],
                "reaction": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                "Unpolarized deuteron beams of energies 14.4 and",
                "9.39 MeV were extracted from the FN tandem Van de",
                "Graaff accelerator. The beams were pulsed at 2 MHz",
                "with a pulse width of 2.0 ns and had time-averaged",
                "intensities of 1.5 nA. The beam traversed a 5.27mg/cm2",
                "Havar foil to enter a 3.16-cm deuterium-filled gas cell",
                "that was held at pressure of 7.8 bar."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "CORRECTION": [
